The renderer seems to force all <form> elements to be new blocks, even though we have defined them to be 'display: inline' via CSS, which does work in browser. For example, this is the structure of the HTML our macro outputs:

{code}
<span><form style="display: inline>...<input...></form></span>
{code}

Post render, it looks like this:

{code}
<p>...<span></span></p>
<form ...>...<input...></form>
{code}

The span is now empty, and the form has been forced outside the paragraph. This makes it difficult to put inline forms into macros...

{code:sql}
select 'Groups',count(*) from groups;
select 'Users',count(*) from users;
{code}

These both return a count of 0, despite working fine in 3.5.1. Originally part of the following usage stats chart

{noformat}
{chart:title=Other Counts|type=bar|displayData=true|width=500|height=300|dataOrientation=vertical|legend=false|tables=counts|attachment=Confluence counts.png}

{sql:dataSource=confluence|width=80|id=counts}
select 'Spaces ' as " ", count(*) as "Count"
from SPACES
union
select 'Contributors' as " ", count(distinct lastmodifier) as "Count"
from CONTENT
union
select 'Users' as " ", count(*) as "Count"
from users
union
select 'Groups' as " ", count(*) as "Count"
from groups
{sql}

{chart}
{noformat}

which (other than changing from os_user to users...) has worked for all Confluence versions since early 2.x versions. It has been working fine in 3.5.1 but in 3.5.6 it fails.

